    "section_image_with_text_VbTWjc": {
      "type": "section-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "image_QcxC8L": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Build_a_Fence.jpg",
            "video": "",
            "video_button_color": "primary",
            "title": "Repair vs Replacement - Which Should I Choose?",
            "desc": "<p>One of the most common questions we’re asked as fence specialists is whether it’s better to repair fencing or replace it entirely. Ultimately, there’s no universal answer to this question, as it depends on a few factors. </p><h3>Extent of Damage </h3><p>For cosmetic damage or loose panels, repairs could be the way to go. If the damage is more extensive, our professionals may recommend a replacement. For example, this might be the case for structural problems, rotting, or if you’ve previously tried repairs only for more problems to arise. </p><h3>Budget </h3><p>Naturally, repairs are the cheaper option of the two, while replacements will require a larger budget. It might be that you want to perform short-term repairs now, and then replace fully when you have the budget. Of course, we’ll always advise if we think your fencing needs a replacement now. <br/></p>",
            "horizontal_align": "left",
            "link_title": "",
            "link": "",
            "bg_color_block": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "bg_color_content": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "color_text": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_heading_color": true,
            "text_border_color": true
          }
        },
        "image_jznGiq": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Chicago_Fence_Installation.png",
            "video": "",
            "video_button_color": "primary",
            "title": "",
            "desc": "<h3>Fence Age </h3><p>If your fence is at an age that we would consider to be the end of its life, the most cost-effective decision in the long term may be a full replacement. On the other hand, a fairly young fence may be the perfect candidate for simple repairs and maintenance. </p><h3>Security </h3><p>Since fencing is pivotal for the security of your property, we may recommend a replacement in cases where we think your fencing leaves you vulnerable. As well as potential crime, poor fencing can open the door to pests. </p><h3>Property Value </h3><p>If you’re planning to sell the property soon, this could impact whether you opt for repair or replacement. With a full replacement, you may just recuperate some of the cost through a higher selling price and increased interest from buyers. <br/><br/>Don’t worry, our specialists can visit your property and provide all the advice you need to decide between repair and replacement. If you have any questions, call our team or pop into our Northbrook showroom today! <br/></p>",
            "horizontal_align": "left",
            "link_title": "",
            "link": "",
            "bg_color_block": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "bg_color_content": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "color_text": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_heading_color": true,
            "text_border_color": true
          }
        }
      },
